      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "If you&#39;re using <code>.split()</code>, pay attention to 2 things: 1 - you&#39;re passing a <b>regular expression</b> as its parameter, 2 - any <b>last empty sections will be discarded</b> unless you pass a 2nd <code>limit</code> parameter (with a value of <code>-1</code> for the most commonly expected result - see here: <a href=\"http://stackoverflow.com/questions/14602062/java-string-split-removed-empty-values\" title=\"java string split removed empty values\">stackoverflow.com/questions/14602062/&hellip;</a>)"
