    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>.split method will work, but it uses regular expressions.  In this example it would be (to steal from Cristian):</p>\n\n<pre><code>String[] separated = CurrentString.split(\"\\\\:\");\nseparated[0]; // this will contain \"Fruit\"\nseparated[1]; // this will contain \" they taste good\"\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Also, this came from:\n<a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/6965642/android-split-not-working-correctly\">Android split not working correctly</a></p>\n"
